in developing countries in two new projects with pesd researchers he will be analyzing how much households internalize the health benefits of improved cookstoves and the effect of energy efficiency improvements on energy consumption sriniketh also has other projects he is currently working on in the environmental arena private and public institutions can play critical roles in the management of fisheries forests and ground water in a project with ecologists and other social scientists he is examining when fishing cooperatives can effectively manage their resources focusing on the case of mexico's gulf of california fisheries in the delivery of services such as food aid health care and education much authority over implementation is devolved to local institutions around the world leading to vast differences in implementation within countries he also has an ongoing project examining the reasons for extraordinarily low take up rates in india's public distribution system which is a major mechanism used to channel food to india's poor search people everything support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 1714 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
